"In Kunar, Pakistan wiped out an entire innocent family on their Eid day. A missile strike killed a female doctor along with her husband, their two children, and their driver. 

These were civilians with no involvement in any conflict. There is no excuse for this. Pakistan must be held accountable for taking innocent lives.
@SR_Afghanistan"

"Horrific reports continue to emerge of Chinese government sending Chinese cadres into Uyghur homes to rape Uyghur women. 

To all who stand for womens rights, justice, and human dignityyour silence in the face of Chinas state-sponsored atrocities against Uyghur women for years, is indefensible. Chinese embassy in the US didnt even hide their crimes and publicly celebrated by tweeting Uyghur women are no longer baby making machines. -please google that and youll see the actual tweet. 

When Uyghur womens bodies are turned into the battlefield of genocide with force sterilization, forced abortion and forced marriages, your silence is not neutrality but it is complicity. You cannot claim credibility in defending justice anywhere if you ignore Uyghur atrocities.

Justice requires leaders who aren't afraid of the cost. I have lost my dear sister to the regime's retaliation for my own advocacy for speaking out, yet I refuse to be silent. I am asking you to have the courage, and please, use your global platforms to lead a movement and be the voice for those who have been stripped of theirs. 

